@startuml
title Platform - Level 1

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

package "Your program" {
	class "main.cpp" as Main
}

package "Sparkle" {
	class Application
	class Window
	class Widget
	class Rendering
}

package "Computer" {
	class "Operating system" as OS
	class "GPU" as GPU
}

Main --> Application : starts
Application --> Window : creates
Window --> OS : owns a real window
OS --> Window : sends close, resize, mouse, keyboard
Widget --> Rendering : describes drawing
Rendering --> GPU : draws pixels
GPU --> Window : presents frame

note bottom
Beginner rule of thumb: user code works with Sparkle
objects. Sparkle talks to the operating system and GPU.
end note

@enduml
